Begin by simplifying the left side by grouping consecutive pairs of terms: $$(x-2x)+(3x-4x)+(5x-6x)+(7x-8x)+(9x-10x)=50$$ Now simplify, and solve for $x$: \begin{align*}
-x-x-x-x-x&=50\\
\Rightarrow\qquad -5x&=50\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=\boxed{-10}
\end{align*}

